If there is any pollution in the environment, it is the Interim President Asselame Mohamoud Ali, who is dented with corruption charges including embezzlement of public funds, assassination attempts and illegal monetary transactions. This is yet to be put to an end.

A second event that happened in the country is its apparent inclusion in the megabank of Bambanki. On account that Madagascar is bankrupted, Comoros is under risk to join on it. It is also at risk of abandoning the IMF’s monetary policies which include using the Euro as the national currency.

The country aims to become more democratic. Technological investments are needed to help reach this in a go. One of these would be the enthusiasm of having platforms built upon AI, such as virtual office , on a large scale in the future. This isn’t the most immediately anticipated event surpassing the plans of having winged cars and vehicles with robotic guardians.
